WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:04.269
<i>Previously on "code black"...</i> I need
you to take over the department.

00:04.271 --> 00:05.571
No. Not a request. Sorry.

00:05.573 --> 00:07.473
I'm not an administrator, ed.
I'm a doctor.

00:07.475 --> 00:08.507
Grace. Neal.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.175
Christa: So, who's grace?

00:10.177 --> 00:12.311
She's a doctor
who used to work here.

00:12.313 --> 00:14.346
I'm asking who she is to<i> you.</i>

00:14.348 --> 00:15.514
You didn't tell her, did you?

00:15.516 --> 00:16.549
Of course not.

00:16.550 --> 00:17.583
You can't tell anyone.
Oh, my God.

00:17.585 --> 00:19.051
Don't pull that knife!

00:19.053 --> 00:21.387
You and I take this
to our graves.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.088
[ Gagging ] Help me.

00:24.625 --> 00:28.427
Angus: ¶ sugar plum fairy
came and hit the streets ¶

00:28.429 --> 00:32.131
¶ looking for soul food
and a place to eat ¶

00:32.133 --> 00:34.199
¶ went to the Apollo ¶

00:34.201 --> 00:36.168
¶ you should've seen 'em
go, go, go ¶

00:36.170 --> 00:40.205
¶ they said, "hey, sugar,
take a walk on the wild side ¶"

00:40.207 --> 00:41.507
Angus: She's testing
the rest of us.

00:41.509 --> 00:44.209
And I don't think
I'm gonna pass that test.

00:44.211 --> 00:47.446
Cole: Started off saving a life,
ended up almost killing someone.

00:47.448 --> 00:48.614
You need to pull!

00:48.616 --> 00:50.215
We need to get a doctor in here.

00:50.217 --> 00:51.250
<i>I'm</i> a doctor.

00:51.252 --> 00:52.535
And you are, too.

00:52.536 --> 00:53.819
Mike: You and I take this
to our graves.

00:53.821 --> 00:55.521
You don't know
how good you are, do you?

00:55.523 --> 00:57.222
Good.

00:57.224 --> 00:59.091
I'm just starting
to get on my feet here.

00:59.093 --> 01:02.761
¶ Doo, doo, doo, doo-doo-doo ¶

01:02.763 --> 01:04.763
[ gasping ]

01:04.765 --> 01:06.432
Heather: Thought you were
gonna run through a wall.

01:06.434 --> 01:08.200
Have you seen those videos
of dogs dreaming?

01:08.202 --> 01:10.102
They're chasing something,
and all of a sudden,

01:10.104 --> 01:13.172
they just wake up, and they run
straight into a wall.

01:13.174 --> 01:14.173
It's hilarious.

01:14.175 --> 01:16.275
Unless you're the dog.

01:16.277 --> 01:19.111
This isn't the best place
to catch a nap, you know.

01:19.113 --> 01:21.180
Icu has a supply closet
they're not using,

01:21.182 --> 01:23.782
and peds has an exam room
with too much lead paint.

01:23.784 --> 01:25.517
Those are the four-star spots.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.353
You okay?

01:28.355 --> 01:30.289
Uh, yeah.

01:30.291 --> 01:31.824
[ Clears throat ]

01:31.826 --> 01:35.494
But, uh, after a cup of coffee,

01:35.496 --> 01:39.298
I am good as... New.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.300
Great.

01:41.302 --> 01:42.302
Here.

01:43.304 --> 01:44.403
What's this?

01:44.405 --> 01:45.337
Adderall.

01:45.339 --> 01:46.872
You have adhd?

01:46.874 --> 01:50.442
No, I'm a surgeon
who works 36-hour shifts.

01:50.444 --> 01:51.844
It'll focus you in.

01:51.846 --> 01:53.812
Silicon valley
runs on this stuff.

01:53.814 --> 01:55.647
Well, I am not Steve Jobs.

01:55.649 --> 01:58.250
You take Tylenol when
you have a headache, right?

01:58.252 --> 01:59.852
[ Pills rattle ] Here.

01:59.854 --> 02:02.588
One for now, one for later...

02:02.590 --> 02:04.189
If you think you need it.

02:04.191 --> 02:05.691
Or<i> don't</i> take it.
It's up to you.

02:05.693 --> 02:08.660
But if you don't take it,
I want them back.

02:08.662 --> 02:10.863
[ Door opens ]

02:10.865 --> 02:12.898
Angus. Let's go.
Shift just started.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.299
It's code red already.

02:14.301 --> 02:16.902
[ Siren wailing ]

02:19.340 --> 02:21.673
We need more nurses, and we need
the ones that we do have

02:21.675 --> 02:23.175
to be paid more money.

02:23.176 --> 02:24.676
You think I haven't
already asked for that?

02:24.678 --> 02:26.445
You weren't
wearing a white coat before.

02:26.447 --> 02:29.348
We waited a long time
for one of us to be one of them.

02:29.350 --> 02:30.800
What do you got?

02:30.801 --> 02:32.251
34-year-old male...
Motorcycle versus tree.

02:32.253 --> 02:34.653
Unresponsive on the scene.
B.P. 60/40.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.688
Stats falling.
Obvious intestinal injury.

02:36.690 --> 02:38.257
Page surgery? Yep.

02:38.259 --> 02:40.292
Center stage. Let's go.

02:41.228 --> 02:42.795
Morning.

02:42.796 --> 02:44.363
[ Door closes ] Good morning.

02:45.332 --> 02:47.466
So, how's Neal doing?
Did he text you?

02:47.468 --> 02:48.867
Nope.

02:48.869 --> 02:50.169
What about you?

02:50.171 --> 02:51.537
Me? No.

02:51.539 --> 02:54.406
I'm sure he's kind of busy.
It's his first O.R. shift.

02:54.408 --> 02:55.674
It's a long one, though, huh?

02:55.676 --> 02:57.092
Yeah.

02:57.093 --> 02:58.509
You guys seem good together.

03:00.281 --> 03:01.346
Thank you.

03:03.250 --> 03:04.283
Nice scarf.

03:05.819 --> 03:07.452
It's beautiful, right?

03:07.454 --> 03:08.954
I take no credit. It's Neal's.

03:08.956 --> 03:10.489
I'm sure it was a gift, though.

03:10.491 --> 03:12.224
It's not like
he has time to go shopping.

03:12.226 --> 03:13.859
Yeah.

03:16.263 --> 03:17.696
Oh, my God. It was from you.

03:17.698 --> 03:20.215
Yeah.

03:20.216 --> 03:22.733
Uh, birthday or... Christmas...
I don't remember.

03:23.804 --> 03:25.270
It looks great on you.

03:29.476 --> 03:30.509
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
Bougie, please.

03:30.511 --> 03:31.977
Jesse: You okay?

03:31.978 --> 03:33.444
Yeah. This airway's
just too anterior.

03:33.447 --> 03:34.546
Here. Thanks.

03:36.584 --> 03:38.417
Sat's in the 80s.

03:38.419 --> 03:39.418
Come on, come on.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.253
I can't see anything in here.

03:41.255 --> 03:43.322
Fishhook, please.
Sorry. Out of hands.

03:43.324 --> 03:45.024
Where are all the nurses?

03:45.025 --> 03:46.725
What have I been telling you?
I'm all you got.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.427
Page surgery. Where's Neal?

03:48.429 --> 03:50.295
Sat's still dropping.

03:50.297 --> 03:52.731
Dr. Lorenson? Can you
come over here for a minute?

03:52.733 --> 03:53.765
Uh, can you get the bag, please?

03:53.767 --> 03:54.600
Here you go.

03:54.602 --> 03:55.834
Bag. Thanks.

03:55.836 --> 03:57.603
Hey, you want to take over here?
Converting.

03:57.605 --> 04:00.372
[ Beeping slows ] Sat's
rising... finally.

04:01.342 --> 04:02.874
About time.

04:02.876 --> 04:04.343
What, did you forget
where the E.R. is?

04:04.345 --> 04:05.989
Too many stairs in this place.

04:05.990 --> 04:07.634
How's Campbell?
I heard he's tough.

04:07.635 --> 04:09.279
He wasn't the one who hired me.
I'm still interviewing.

04:09.283 --> 04:10.449
What do you have?

04:10.451 --> 04:11.450
Leanne: Disembowelment.

04:11.452 --> 04:12.351
Any other injuries?

04:12.353 --> 04:13.919
Don't see any yet.

04:13.921 --> 04:15.621
Okay, run it down for me.

04:15.623 --> 04:17.523
I've got it.

04:17.524 --> 04:19.424
Dr. Rorish, would you please
run it down for me?

04:20.327 --> 04:22.494
Sir, traumatic disembowelment.

04:23.497 --> 04:26.031
All right, Dr. Hudson,
let's move him. Come on.

04:26.033 --> 04:27.866
Let's go.

04:27.868 --> 04:30.435
No, I really can handle this.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.437
Dr. Hudson,
you're a new attending.

04:32.439 --> 04:34.373
You shadow me until I know
what you're capable of.

04:34.375 --> 04:37.743
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

04:37.745 --> 04:39.778
[ Screams ]

04:41.015 --> 04:42.881
[ People murmuring ]

04:42.883 --> 04:45.784
[ Screams ]
[ Indistinct shouting ]

04:45.786 --> 04:46.918
Man: Let's go, let's go!

04:46.920 --> 04:48.320
Hannah: Oh, my God.

04:48.322 --> 04:50.756
Security! Doctors!

04:50.758 --> 04:51.723
Someone help!

04:51.725 --> 04:53.058
[ Gasping ]

04:53.060 --> 04:55.360
Move, move, move!
Drop it! Drop the ax!

04:55.362 --> 04:56.561
[ Gun cocks ] You heard him! Drop it!
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

04:56.563 --> 04:57.729
Don't shoot me.

05:00.401 --> 05:01.917
Please, don't... don't shoot.

05:01.918 --> 05:03.478
[ Whimpering ]
Oh, my leg is killing me.

05:05.005 --> 05:05.937
Your<i> leg?</i>

05:05.939 --> 05:07.839
It's makeup.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.041
I'm a zombie.

05:09.043 --> 05:10.442
Man: We were at a convention.

05:10.444 --> 05:11.877
We're not the only ones
coming in.

05:11.879 --> 05:13.879
There was an accident.
Some scaffolding collapsed.

05:13.881 --> 05:15.047
I'm sorry if we scared you.

05:15.049 --> 05:17.482
Sure. No problem, ma'am.

05:18.652 --> 05:19.818
Can you handle this, please?

05:20.988 --> 05:23.889
[ People murmuring ]

05:23.891 --> 05:25.524
What the hell?

05:26.694 --> 05:27.726
Excuse me.

05:29.530 --> 05:31.330
I'm the event medic
from the convention.

05:31.332 --> 05:32.665
We used one of our shuttles

05:32.666 --> 05:33.999
to bring in
some of the minor injuries.

05:34.001 --> 05:35.761
There were two rigs on the scene
when I left.

05:37.905 --> 05:39.538
[ Sighing ] Oh, God.

05:39.540 --> 05:41.606
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:47.514 --> 05:49.264
We just love zombies,

05:49.265 --> 05:51.015
wanted to find a way
to celebrate that.

05:51.018 --> 05:52.918
Ow! [ Inhales sharply ]

05:52.920 --> 05:54.519
That really hurts.

05:54.521 --> 05:56.421
I'll give you some more
Lidocaine for the pain.

05:56.423 --> 05:57.589
Is she gonna be okay?

05:57.591 --> 05:59.524
Yeah. It's mostly lacerations.

05:59.526 --> 06:01.460
No fractures.

06:01.462 --> 06:03.929
So, what's your favorite
zombie movie?

06:03.931 --> 06:05.464
"Dawn of the dead."
"Dawn of the dead."

06:05.466 --> 06:06.631
Totally, right?

06:06.633 --> 06:09.134
Although "dead alive"...
Crazy-good.

06:09.136 --> 06:10.135
Beyond.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.770
Never wanted to eat soup again.

06:11.772 --> 06:13.472
Oh, my God. Who are you?

06:14.475 --> 06:17.409
8-year-old boy complaining of
abdominal pain, modest guarding.

06:17.411 --> 06:18.543
Stable b.P. In the field.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.195
Dr. Savetti, over here.

06:20.196 --> 06:21.846
Son, can you hear me?
Yeah. I'm okay.

06:21.849 --> 06:23.782
44-year-old male
with significant crush injury,

06:23.784 --> 06:26.451
multiple chest deformities,
difficulty breathing.

06:26.453 --> 06:27.519
My dad was with me.

06:27.521 --> 06:29.388
Bed 3. Dad?!

06:29.390 --> 06:30.622
I'm right here, Luke.

06:30.624 --> 06:31.957
Dr. Leighton, you're with me.

06:31.959 --> 06:34.993
Blood pressure crashing, 60/40.

06:34.995 --> 06:37.763
Luke: We were at this really
cool zombie thing, right, dad?

06:37.765 --> 06:39.030
We were having so much fun.
Okay, ready?

06:39.032 --> 06:40.766
And then there was this crash.

06:40.768 --> 06:43.535
1, 2, 3. My dad grabbed me.

06:44.538 --> 06:46.071
Dad?! Are you there?!

06:46.073 --> 06:47.256
Is he okay?!

06:47.257 --> 06:48.440
I've barely got a pulse here.

06:48.442 --> 06:49.841
Ready? 1, 2, 3.

06:49.843 --> 06:50.876
[ Breathes shakily ]

06:50.878 --> 06:52.944
It was all
supposed to be pretend.

07:04.024 --> 07:06.758
There's blood everywhere. Some
of these scalp wounds are real.

07:06.760 --> 07:07.926
Which ones
are actually bleeding?

07:07.927 --> 07:09.093
I can't tell.
There's too much fake blood.

07:09.096 --> 07:09.928
Peroxide.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.696
Huh?

07:11.698 --> 07:13.665
It dissolves real blood.
Here. Look.

07:13.667 --> 07:16.067
Watch for the foamy bubbles there.
See? Nice.

07:16.069 --> 07:18.437
All right, I need suction
and a skin stapler.

07:18.439 --> 07:19.471
Where'd you pull
that trick from?

07:19.473 --> 07:21.089
Summer camp.

07:21.090 --> 07:22.706
Lac stabilized.
Let's roll him for X-Ray.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.910
1...2... 3.

07:24.912 --> 07:26.111
Easy.

07:26.113 --> 07:28.447
Everything's going to be okay,
right?

07:28.449 --> 07:30.215
Just hang in there, young vato.

07:30.217 --> 07:33.718
This is the best hospital
for zombies<i> and</i> humans, okay?

07:33.720 --> 07:35.303
Easy, now.

07:35.304 --> 07:36.887
Luke, do you feel any pain
when I press here?

07:36.890 --> 07:38.774
No. I'm okay.

07:38.775 --> 07:40.659
We've got free fluid.
Possible splenic laceration.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.494
Sir, sir. Are you still with us?

07:42.496 --> 07:45.063
Where's Luke? He's my son.

07:45.065 --> 07:46.031
He's right next to you.

07:46.033 --> 07:47.533
Over here, dad!

07:47.534 --> 07:49.034
Diaphragm rupture.
Get surgery down here now.

07:49.036 --> 07:50.352
Ready for liftoff?

07:50.353 --> 07:51.669
Cole: All right,
let's get him up to C.T.

07:51.672 --> 07:52.504
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

07:52.506 --> 07:53.772
[ Gurgles ] Dad!

07:53.774 --> 07:55.807
Mike: Oh, God. Are you okay?!

07:55.809 --> 07:56.975
All right, hematemesis.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.009
I need an airway ready. Dad!

07:58.011 --> 07:59.511
Somebody call the O.R.

07:59.513 --> 08:02.747
Get the kid moving!
Let's go, let's go!

08:02.749 --> 08:03.849
Dad! Come on, son.

08:08.055 --> 08:09.788
Psst!

08:09.790 --> 08:12.023
Hey. You see that yellow tag
on the chart?

08:12.025 --> 08:12.924
V.I.P.

08:12.926 --> 08:14.943
[ Scoffs ] Lucky me.

08:14.944 --> 08:16.961
Big donors. They have
a whole floor named after them.

08:16.964 --> 08:19.030
Made their money
on a huge pet-food website.

08:19.032 --> 08:20.532
Not that you're checking.

08:20.534 --> 08:21.833
Listen, my advice is to hurry.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.702
The suits are gonna be down here
soon enough.

08:29.009 --> 08:30.709
Robert: Yeah, yeah.
Listen, I got to go.

08:30.711 --> 08:33.111
Hello. I'm Dr. Pineda.
What brings you here?

08:33.113 --> 08:34.563
My husband needs his phone

08:34.564 --> 08:36.014
surgically detached
from his ear.

08:36.016 --> 08:36.848
I'll speak to you Tuesday.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.083
Sorry. I'm sorry.

08:38.085 --> 08:39.918
Sunday's actually
a workday for me.

08:39.919 --> 08:41.752
They<i> all</i> are. And I told you
that you didn't need to come.

08:41.755 --> 08:43.188
And let you skip
tomorrow's mediation?

08:43.190 --> 08:44.856
You missed
the last two meetings...

08:44.858 --> 08:46.491
Which I had to pay for.

08:46.492 --> 08:48.125
We are in the middle
of a cooperative divorce.

08:48.128 --> 08:50.368
If you were cooperative,
we wouldn't be getting divorced.

08:51.131 --> 08:54.199
So, Mrs. Stein,
uh, what are you here for today?

08:54.201 --> 08:55.667
I'm having stomach pains.

08:55.669 --> 08:56.768
It's always something.

08:56.770 --> 08:58.320
Do you think
I want to be in the E.R.?

08:58.321 --> 08:59.871
Honestly, Susan,
I don't know<i> what</i> you want.

08:59.873 --> 09:02.574
Ohh! Ow!

09:02.576 --> 09:04.643
It's okay.
Tell me exactly where it hurts.

09:04.645 --> 09:06.945
Can you get Dr. Rorish?

09:08.048 --> 09:10.315
Uh, Dr. Rorish is
in administration now,

09:10.317 --> 09:12.651
and I'm perfectly capable...
I'm calling harbert.

09:12.653 --> 09:14.719
[ Groaning ]

09:14.721 --> 09:16.655
Feel the trachea.
I think I'm in.

09:16.657 --> 09:17.289
You<i> think?</i>

09:17.291 --> 09:18.607
You need more suction?

09:18.608 --> 09:19.924
Yeah, I can't see anything
with this blood.

09:19.927 --> 09:21.593
He's not in.
Stats are still dropping.

09:21.595 --> 09:23.161
Mike: All right.
It's a tough airway.

09:23.162 --> 09:24.728
Let me try.
I'll grab a d.L. And a bougie.

09:24.731 --> 09:25.931
I got one.

09:25.933 --> 09:27.132
Hey.

09:27.134 --> 09:28.733
You carry an extra bougie
in your pocket?

09:28.735 --> 09:30.135
Angus, you're never gonna
see anything down there.

09:30.137 --> 09:32.154
There's too much blood.

09:32.155 --> 09:34.172
A bit more. I've got the cords.

09:34.174 --> 09:35.840
I'm... In.

09:35.842 --> 09:36.841
[ Monitor beeping ]

09:36.843 --> 09:38.076
Bag him up.

09:38.078 --> 09:39.711
Sats improving. Nice job.

09:39.713 --> 09:41.146
Great, man.

09:41.148 --> 09:43.148
Heather: Dr. Leighton,
what do we have?

09:43.149 --> 09:45.149
We've got a crush injury,
severe gastric bleeding.

09:45.152 --> 09:47.152
Concerned for diaphragm rupture.

09:47.154 --> 09:48.620
Okay. How much blood loss?

09:48.621 --> 09:50.087
300 cc. His airway is secure.

09:50.090 --> 09:51.656
Okay. Let's prep him
for transport.

09:52.826 --> 09:55.060
Jesse: Taking out the scope.

09:58.298 --> 09:59.864
Leslie: Oh, my God.

09:59.866 --> 10:01.700
Luke, what happened?

10:01.702 --> 10:03.101
Are you family? Yes.

10:03.103 --> 10:05.036
There was an incident
that happened at the...

10:05.038 --> 10:06.671
I told them
not to go to that thing.

10:06.673 --> 10:09.174
No, Luke here is
gonna be just fine, but...

10:09.176 --> 10:11.309
But what? Where's Ben?

10:11.311 --> 10:13.044
He was sent up to the O.R.

10:13.046 --> 10:14.629
Oh, my God.

10:14.630 --> 10:16.213
Listen, I know
this is a lot to take in,

10:16.216 --> 10:18.950
but we need to know if he has
any other medical problems.

10:18.952 --> 10:20.318
That would help the surgeons
right now.

10:20.320 --> 10:23.655
Uh, no. No. I don't think so.

10:23.657 --> 10:25.790
No, no other problems.
He's healthy.

10:27.394 --> 10:29.894
Luke? You okay?

10:29.896 --> 10:31.763
Luke? Listen, listen.

10:31.765 --> 10:33.865
I know this is tough,

10:33.867 --> 10:36.201
but the boy needs to see you
being strong.

10:36.203 --> 10:37.736
Okay?

10:37.738 --> 10:39.137
Okay.

10:39.139 --> 10:42.907
Luke, I'm gonna let you and
your mother spend some time...

10:42.909 --> 10:44.309
She's<i> not</i> my mom.

10:46.913 --> 10:48.880
I'm Ben's fiancée.

10:51.218 --> 10:53.151
We're supposed to be
getting married next week.

10:59.960 --> 11:01.393
[ Sighs ]

11:03.296 --> 11:05.113
I texted you.

11:05.114 --> 11:06.931
I saw three dots,
like you were typing something,

11:06.933 --> 11:08.433
and then they just went away.

11:09.403 --> 11:11.370
Yeah?

11:11.371 --> 11:13.338
I guess I realized
that I had nothing to say.

11:14.307 --> 11:16.307
See, this is why
we're not hooking up anymore.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.680
Well.

11:21.682 --> 11:23.081
That explains a lot.

11:26.186 --> 11:28.053
Let's go, guys.
We have to get him upstairs.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.356
This is beyond simple,

11:31.358 --> 11:33.358
and I'm not sure why
we're still talking about it.

11:33.360 --> 11:34.860
Because it's dangerous.

11:34.861 --> 11:36.361
It's dangerous that the steins
want you to be their doctor?

11:36.363 --> 11:37.796
Not just that.

11:37.797 --> 11:39.230
You want an elite experience
for them,

11:39.232 --> 11:41.833
but this isn't
an airline loyalty program.

11:41.835 --> 11:43.435
Exactly. [ Chuckles ]

11:43.437 --> 11:44.836
It is much more important

11:44.838 --> 11:46.471
that these people
helped modernize angels.

11:46.473 --> 11:48.373
These are investments that we all
benefit from. You know the data.

11:48.375 --> 11:51.309
V.I.P. Treatment in a hospital
can be dangerous.

11:51.311 --> 11:53.078
Protocols get sidestepped.

11:53.080 --> 11:55.246
Safety measures
fall through the cracks.

11:55.248 --> 11:57.282
That's why medical mistakes
happen so often

11:57.284 --> 11:58.383
with famous patients.

11:58.385 --> 12:00.218
Then<i> I'll</i> take the case.

12:00.220 --> 12:01.920
My scrubs
are still in the closet.

12:01.922 --> 12:04.923
Oh, well, while you're in there,
see if you can hire more nurses.

12:04.925 --> 12:06.391
My people are working
way too hard.

12:06.393 --> 12:08.376
More nurses?

12:08.377 --> 12:10.360
This is angels.
We<i> all</i> work way too hard.

12:10.363 --> 12:11.696
We don't have enough money.

12:11.697 --> 12:13.030
Why do you think
we're always in code black?

12:13.033 --> 12:15.467
Because you people
think like suits.

12:15.469 --> 12:17.302
You don't understand our needs.

12:20.006 --> 12:22.173
Despite the scrubs
you're wearing,

12:22.175 --> 12:23.341
you are a suit now, too, leanne.

12:23.343 --> 12:24.909
The budgets...
Have you read them yet?

12:24.911 --> 12:26.277
I am making my way through them.

12:26.279 --> 12:28.413
It's not exactly a page-Turner.

12:28.415 --> 12:30.315
Ironic that
there is a man out there

12:30.317 --> 12:32.917
who could get you nurses
<i>tomorrow.</i>

12:32.919 --> 12:35.386
He's sitting with his wife,
but you won't see them.

12:35.388 --> 12:37.355
Did it ever occur to you

12:37.357 --> 12:39.390
that you don't
have to buy these people?

12:39.392 --> 12:41.493
Maybe they give out of the
kindness of their hearts.

12:43.130 --> 12:44.129
No.

12:44.131 --> 12:45.330
Good day, doctor.

12:46.933 --> 12:48.366
[ Door opens ]

12:50.370 --> 12:51.820
[ Door closes ]

12:51.821 --> 12:53.271
16-year-old boy.
Fell downstairs.

12:53.273 --> 12:54.806
Minor burns, no k.O.

12:54.808 --> 12:56.141
Hey. How you doing, buddy?

12:56.143 --> 12:58.176
Fine. I fell.
This is all probably overkill.

12:58.178 --> 12:59.410
Did you see the incident, sir?

12:59.412 --> 13:01.012
No, I didn't. And who are you?

13:01.014 --> 13:02.447
Craig James. I run a boot camp
for troubled teens.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.299
He's one of my campers.

13:04.300 --> 13:06.150
Sorry, Mr. James. I'm sorry
to be a problem like this.

13:06.153 --> 13:08.086
Anything else you can tell us?
Nothing.

13:08.088 --> 13:09.454
We were out
doing our morning workout,

13:09.456 --> 13:11.322
and he came back
looking like this.

13:11.324 --> 13:12.924
[ Gasps ]

13:12.926 --> 13:16.361
Dr. Lorenson, why don't you
take a look at his injuries?

13:16.363 --> 13:18.797
I am going to start
the paperwork with you, sir,

13:18.799 --> 13:20.677
right here.

13:20.678 --> 13:22.556
So, if he disappeared, why
didn't you go looking for him?

13:22.557 --> 13:24.435
We did. The last place we thought
he'd go back to was the dorms.

13:24.437 --> 13:26.237
He's tried to run away
before, so...

13:26.239 --> 13:27.405
[ Groans ]

13:27.407 --> 13:29.440
These bruises
on your face and arms...

13:29.442 --> 13:30.909
How did you get them?

13:30.910 --> 13:32.377
Uh, it's, uh,
really dumb, actually.

13:32.379 --> 13:34.112
I fell down some stairs.

13:35.415 --> 13:37.949
And these circular burns
on your arms...

13:37.951 --> 13:39.918
Did someone do this to you?

13:39.920 --> 13:43.254
No. I, uh, messed up the campfire
one night. It's all good.

13:43.256 --> 13:45.423
I don't understand how
you got these from a campfire.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.158
Aah! O-okay, all right, okay.

13:47.160 --> 13:48.226
Does that hurt? Yeah, yeah.

13:48.228 --> 13:50.461
Okay, hang on. Okay. All right.

13:50.463 --> 13:51.429
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

13:51.431 --> 13:53.264
Okay, Brody,
don't move your arm.

13:53.266 --> 13:55.099
You have
a really serious fracture.

13:55.101 --> 13:56.434
Where are his parents?

13:56.436 --> 13:58.136
New York. And he's not allowed
to talk to them.

13:58.138 --> 14:00.171
Those are the rules.
It's tough, I know.

14:00.173 --> 14:02.240
We push them hard,
and sometimes this even works.

14:02.242 --> 14:03.541
These are bad kids.

14:03.543 --> 14:07.178
Do you want to explain to me
how this boy came in here

14:07.180 --> 14:10.248
with burns, dehydration,
and a proximal humeral fracture?

14:10.250 --> 14:13.017
What are you accusing me of?

14:14.421 --> 14:16.354
What are you telling them?

14:16.356 --> 14:17.722
I didn't say anything to anyone.

14:17.723 --> 14:19.089
You're starting to mess
with too many people.

14:19.092 --> 14:20.108
Okay, that's enough.

14:20.109 --> 14:21.469
Hannah,
can you take this gentleman

14:23.396 --> 14:24.395
to registration, please?

14:24.396 --> 14:25.395
Dr. Lorenson,
you with me... now.

14:25.398 --> 14:26.898
[ Scoffs ]

14:32.205 --> 14:33.788
I don't understand
how you can be pissed

14:33.789 --> 14:35.372
when I'm doing exactly
what I<i> should</i> be doing.

14:35.375 --> 14:38.309
We don't make conclusions like
that 30 seconds into the exam.

14:38.311 --> 14:40.195
You weren't in the exam.
It doesn't matter.

14:40.196 --> 14:42.080
Irrespective of what you found,
you led with your feelings.

14:42.082 --> 14:43.414
My<i> feelings?</i>

14:43.416 --> 14:44.916
You don't confront people
like that.

14:44.918 --> 14:46.584
This whole thing just exploded.

14:46.586 --> 14:47.919
It's unacceptable.

14:48.655 --> 14:50.655
With all due respect,
I was a doctor

14:50.657 --> 14:53.558
responding to information
that you weren't privy to.

14:53.560 --> 14:55.293
Now, are you upset
about something else,

14:55.295 --> 14:57.095
or is that it?

14:57.097 --> 14:58.196
If I were you,

14:58.198 --> 15:00.265
I'd keep your mind
on the medicine.

15:10.977 --> 15:12.143
Have you seen the chart
for my peds patient?

15:12.145 --> 15:15.079
I know I left it here somewhere.
Nope.

15:15.081 --> 15:17.215
His name is Elliot lautner.
He has croup.

15:17.217 --> 15:19.417
I said I haven't seen it.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.319
[ Slams folder ]

15:25.558 --> 15:27.058
Hey.

15:27.060 --> 15:31.296
You know that Neal isn't
interested in her anymore, right?

15:32.933 --> 15:34.365
Here it is.

15:37.003 --> 15:39.637
Will: So, this guy got injured
at a zombie convention?

15:39.639 --> 15:41.205
Is that a thing?

15:41.207 --> 15:45.410
Dr. Hudson, you could at least
<i>try</i> to keep up with me.

15:45.412 --> 15:46.377
I can help.

15:46.379 --> 15:47.578
It's fine. I've got it.

15:47.580 --> 15:48.579
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

15:48.581 --> 15:50.415
B.P. Is dropping. He's unstable.

15:50.417 --> 15:51.582
It's an intercostal bleed.

15:51.584 --> 15:53.051
Well, hold down this vessel.

15:53.053 --> 15:54.519
Here. Yeah.

15:54.521 --> 15:56.688
Ligate here. Okay,
now tie it off proximately.

15:56.690 --> 15:58.523
[ Beeping continues ]

16:02.195 --> 16:03.394
Another suture, please.

16:03.396 --> 16:04.963
You didn't close it down enough.

16:04.965 --> 16:06.998
You got one more shot
at this bleed, Dr. Hudson.

16:08.335 --> 16:10.101
The problem here
is this shiny structure,

16:10.103 --> 16:11.636
the vagus nerve.

16:11.637 --> 16:13.170
What's gonna happen if
Dr. Hudson cuts it, Dr. pinkney?

16:13.173 --> 16:14.672
The nerve supply to the heart
and lungs will be cut off.

16:14.674 --> 16:16.507
And we're running out of time.

16:16.509 --> 16:18.543
His pressure is dangerously low.

16:18.545 --> 16:20.278
Let's see how fast
you can tie this up.

16:20.280 --> 16:22.013
I'm sure Dr. Hudson has done it
hundreds of times.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.148
He's not a resident.

16:23.149 --> 16:24.282
Well, then,
he won't mind doing it again.

16:24.284 --> 16:26.117
Of course not.

16:26.119 --> 16:27.685
Cut here, please.

16:27.687 --> 16:29.187
[ Snip ]

16:29.189 --> 16:30.321
[ Beeping stops ] Done.

16:30.323 --> 16:33.124
Bleeding's stopped,
nerve is safe,

16:33.126 --> 16:35.259
and blood pressure
coming back up.

16:35.261 --> 16:38.229
All right.
Close it up for me, will you?

16:40.667 --> 16:42.166
Harbert:
Well, we cleared it out.

16:42.168 --> 16:43.601
I had you moved in here

16:43.602 --> 16:45.035
as soon as I found out
that you arrived.

16:45.038 --> 16:46.554
You'll have more privacy.

16:46.555 --> 16:48.071
We got some food coming in
from across the street.

16:48.074 --> 16:49.774
Where's the minibar, ed?

16:49.776 --> 16:51.342
That's very funny.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.277
So, you have cramps and nausea.

16:53.279 --> 16:55.213
Mm-hmm. Is this real,

16:55.215 --> 16:57.048
or is it just, like,
bad Sushi or something?

16:57.050 --> 16:58.716
Maybe you should go home.

16:58.718 --> 17:01.252
Oh, so you can tell your lawyer
that I left you here all alone?

17:01.254 --> 17:02.654
No, thanks.

17:02.655 --> 17:04.055
Harbert: I've already put in
for a C.T. scan.

17:04.057 --> 17:06.324
I'll get you
one of our g.I. Specialists.

17:06.326 --> 17:08.559
Here. We'll need a urine
sample... pregnancy test.

17:08.561 --> 17:10.545
Oh, she's not pregnant.

17:10.546 --> 17:12.530
Did you have a tubal ligation,
a hysterectomy?

17:12.532 --> 17:15.300
No.

17:15.301 --> 17:18.069
Look, we've been trying to get
pregnant for years now, okay?

17:18.071 --> 17:20.304
A fertility doctor bought
a new house with our money.

17:20.306 --> 17:22.073
A pregnancy test is standard.

17:22.075 --> 17:24.308
Dr. Pineda, let's skip it.

17:24.310 --> 17:25.576
Yeah, trust me...
She'd have a better chance

17:25.578 --> 17:27.245
with a powerball ticket.

17:27.247 --> 17:28.279
Give me the damn cup.

17:32.452 --> 17:33.718
I<i> might</i> be pregnant.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.319
Excuse me?

17:35.321 --> 17:37.288
I know it's not mine.
You're already screwing someone?

17:37.290 --> 17:39.323
Oh, you're an idiot.

17:39.325 --> 17:40.825
One thing we never did
was lie to each other.

17:40.827 --> 17:43.594
I implanted
the last two embryos.

17:43.596 --> 17:46.164
What? Without telling me?

17:46.166 --> 17:48.599
What do you care?
You're leaving.

17:48.601 --> 17:50.368
Those are<i> my</i> embryos, too!

17:50.370 --> 17:51.469
Maybe we'll give you a minute.

17:51.471 --> 17:52.837
Oh, we're gonna need
more than a minute.

17:52.839 --> 17:55.440
Take as many as you want.
Dr. Pineda.

17:58.611 --> 17:59.677
[ Monitor beeping ]

18:04.717 --> 18:06.384
I should have told you
about Heather.

18:06.386 --> 18:08.553
Why would you tell me?
We weren't dating.

18:09.689 --> 18:11.089
It still hurts.

18:13.860 --> 18:16.260
Can I get more of that?

18:16.262 --> 18:17.395
Yeah, Sandy.

18:18.398 --> 18:19.998
Thank you.

18:19.999 --> 18:21.599
I'll, uh, get some more saline
for the irrigation.

18:21.601 --> 18:23.267
I'll be right back.

18:25.371 --> 18:26.337
I'll be back.

18:26.339 --> 18:28.306
Angus.

18:28.308 --> 18:30.374
It's over with us anyway.
She drove me crazy.

18:30.376 --> 18:32.410
She kept blocking me,
then unblocking me.

18:32.412 --> 18:34.445
She was screwing Campbell
at the same time.

18:34.447 --> 18:35.580
Oh, my God! I know, right?

18:35.582 --> 18:37.381
We are not doing this.

18:37.383 --> 18:40.118
Have you heard her laugh?
It's more of a cackle.

18:40.120 --> 18:42.386
She has no idea how to roll down
a tube of toothpaste.

18:42.388 --> 18:44.755
I mean, surgeon? Really?

18:44.757 --> 18:45.756
I don't care.

18:45.758 --> 18:46.757
What?

18:46.759 --> 18:49.460
I don't... Care.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.395
And, by the way,
you can't be this annoyed

18:51.397 --> 18:52.597
with someone you<i> don't</i> like.

18:52.599 --> 18:55.233
Dr. Leighton. You got a minute?

18:55.235 --> 18:56.267
Yeah.

18:57.403 --> 19:00.304
How's, uh, Ben barton doing?

19:00.306 --> 19:02.306
Just got out of the O.R.

19:02.308 --> 19:04.342
He's in critical condition,
but he should pull through.

19:04.344 --> 19:06.210
Ah. That's great work
by the team.

19:06.212 --> 19:09.380
Angus, he's alive
'cause you were prepared.

19:09.382 --> 19:11.349
You nailed that airway, man.
I'm proud of you.

19:11.351 --> 19:15.353
Well, I'm, uh, still working on
taking a compliment,

19:15.355 --> 19:17.255
but, um, thank you.

19:17.257 --> 19:19.390
Well, whatever you're doing,
just keep doing it.

19:19.392 --> 19:20.691
[ Pats ] We're all noticing.

19:20.693 --> 19:22.460
You know what<i> I'm</i> noticing?
What?

19:22.462 --> 19:23.461
That beard.

19:23.463 --> 19:25.229
Long shifts.

19:25.231 --> 19:26.631
[ Door opens ]

19:26.633 --> 19:28.699
[ Radio chatter ]

19:35.175 --> 19:36.274
[ Coughing ]

19:36.276 --> 19:37.876
Christa: What's happening?

19:37.877 --> 19:39.477
He suddenly started vomiting.
Heart rate in the hundreds.

19:39.479 --> 19:40.578
Help. I don't know
what's wrong with me.

19:40.580 --> 19:41.746
Okay, that's why I'm here.

19:41.748 --> 19:43.414
Start fluids. Give 4 of zofran.

19:43.416 --> 19:45.449
Did we get an EKG
with that heart rate?

19:45.451 --> 19:48.452
EKG normal.
Rhythm, blood gas unremarkable.

19:48.454 --> 19:50.454
And no evidence of
internal bleeding on the c.T.S?

19:50.456 --> 19:51.455
No.

19:51.457 --> 19:53.441
I think I'm hyperventilating.

19:53.442 --> 19:55.426
Okay. Just take deep breaths
for me, all right? Okay.

19:55.428 --> 19:56.944
Okay. Okay.

19:56.945 --> 19:58.461
That should
make you feel better.

19:58.464 --> 19:59.931
[ Breathing deeply ] Okay. Okay.

20:00.533 --> 20:01.933
Okay.

20:05.638 --> 20:07.405
Snuck off by yourself, huh?

20:08.541 --> 20:10.942
Everybody else was outside.

20:10.944 --> 20:12.877
Yeah.

20:12.879 --> 20:15.646
I left.
I just wanted to go home.

20:15.648 --> 20:18.416
Home like your bunk or...?

20:18.418 --> 20:19.450
Home.

20:21.588 --> 20:23.988
[ Voice breaking ]
I can't take it anymore.

20:23.990 --> 20:25.556
We have to wake up
at 5:00 in the morning,

20:25.558 --> 20:26.991
run for an hour and a half,

20:26.993 --> 20:28.693
pick up tires, run with those.

20:28.695 --> 20:31.896
He put me on nothing
but white rice and beans.

20:31.898 --> 20:33.331
He doesn't give me water.

20:33.333 --> 20:34.265
Okay.

20:34.267 --> 20:35.466
Has he hit you?

20:35.468 --> 20:36.634
[ Breathes shakily ]

20:36.636 --> 20:38.302
I don't want to get in trouble.

20:38.304 --> 20:40.771
You won't. I promise.
Tell me the truth.

20:40.773 --> 20:42.940
I'm so scared.

20:42.942 --> 20:44.408
That's probably why
you've been vomiting.

20:44.410 --> 20:46.077
[ Whimpers ]

20:46.078 --> 20:47.838
Tell me the truth.
He can't hurt you anymore.

20:50.550 --> 20:53.451
He burns me every night
with his cigarettes.

20:53.453 --> 20:54.785
[ Sobs ]

20:54.787 --> 20:56.287
He threw me across the room.

20:56.289 --> 20:57.488
That's what happened to my arm.

20:57.490 --> 20:59.523
Please, don't make me
go back there.

20:59.525 --> 21:00.858
Okay. Shh.

21:00.860 --> 21:03.427
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ] Please!
Okay, okay.

21:03.429 --> 21:04.895
Shh. [ Grunting ]

21:04.897 --> 21:06.564
Patient seizing in bed 6!

21:06.566 --> 21:08.432
I need 1 of ativan now!

21:08.434 --> 21:10.701
Okay. All right, Brody.

21:10.703 --> 21:12.536
Okay, Brody. Just breathe.

21:12.538 --> 21:13.537
[ Grunting ] Just breathe.

21:13.539 --> 21:15.640
[ Conversing in French ]

21:39.299 --> 21:40.665
Grace!

21:40.667 --> 21:42.066
Dr. Adams.

21:42.068 --> 21:45.002
Just finishing our post-op.

21:45.003 --> 21:47.937
Dr. Campbell does not believe
these are my old legs.

21:47.940 --> 21:50.007
[ Laughing ] Oh. Well, I'll just
have to set him straight.

21:50.009 --> 21:54.478
Roseline is doing much better
than expected.

21:54.480 --> 21:55.813
She's got a great spirit.

21:55.815 --> 21:57.782
Yeah, and she seems
to like you, too.

21:58.918 --> 22:00.084
What about you?

22:00.086 --> 22:02.320
[ Chuckles ] Do I like you?

22:02.322 --> 22:03.821
Do you like schubert?

22:03.823 --> 22:06.924
I have tickets to
the philharmonic this Saturday.

22:06.926 --> 22:08.759
Roseline, ready for our post-op?

22:08.761 --> 22:11.395
Dr. Campbell beat you to it.

22:11.397 --> 22:12.663
Of course he did.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.366
I better get going.

22:19.672 --> 22:22.573
Dr. Adams, let me know
about the concert this weekend.

22:28.581 --> 22:29.513
Hey, Luke.

22:29.515 --> 22:31.115
Is my dad coming to see me?

22:31.117 --> 22:33.017
Not yet. How is he?

22:33.019 --> 22:35.019
Well, he suffered
a gastric hernia,

22:35.021 --> 22:36.404
so he's still critical.

22:36.405 --> 22:37.788
A hernia doesn't sound that bad.

22:37.790 --> 22:39.657
His stomach
translocated to his chest

22:39.659 --> 22:42.126
and required a massive revision
to his diaphragm,

22:42.128 --> 22:44.395
so next few hours
will tell us a lot.

22:44.397 --> 22:46.030
What are you guys talking about?

22:46.032 --> 22:47.665
That's a lot of fancy words
to say

22:47.667 --> 22:49.967
we're trying to do
everything we can for your dad.

22:51.604 --> 22:52.870
Can we go home tonight?

22:52.872 --> 22:55.039
Oh, sweetheart...
I didn't ask<i> you.</i>

22:56.542 --> 22:58.909
Your dad is still
very sick, Luke.

22:58.911 --> 23:01.045
Why can't you make him better?

23:01.047 --> 23:03.114
Well, that's what
we're trying to do, son.

23:03.116 --> 23:04.482
How's he doing, Jesse?

23:04.484 --> 23:06.650
This one? Like a champ.

23:06.652 --> 23:08.586
His last set of hemoglobins
came back steady.

23:08.588 --> 23:10.321
Good. That's good.

23:10.322 --> 23:12.055
We want to keep an eye
on your spleen,

23:12.058 --> 23:14.658
just to make sure
that everything's okay.

23:14.660 --> 23:16.694
I'm sure your dad
wants to see you, too.

23:16.696 --> 23:19.830
Best thing you can do for him
right now is to be strong.

23:19.832 --> 23:21.632
Leslie's gonna stay with you
for a little...

23:21.634 --> 23:23.000
Don't want her with me!

23:23.002 --> 23:24.602
I'll just sit here quietly...

23:24.604 --> 23:26.537
No! Go away!

23:26.539 --> 23:29.673
You're not in my family!
I don't<i> want</i> you in my family!

23:29.675 --> 23:32.443
Don't you think
I care about your dad, too?

23:32.445 --> 23:34.812
That I love him, too?

23:36.949 --> 23:39.483
I'm sorry
that upsets you so much.

23:43.756 --> 23:46.824
Luke, I know a lot of grown-ups
are talking to you,

23:46.826 --> 23:48.192
and that can get confusing.

23:48.194 --> 23:49.593
I just want you to know

23:49.595 --> 23:51.829
that everybody's trying
to help you, son.

23:57.503 --> 23:59.703
I guess you don't want
a new mom, huh?

24:00.740 --> 24:02.306
No.

24:02.307 --> 24:03.873
Yeah, I wouldn't want one,
either.

24:06.446 --> 24:09.580
But you know
what I can always use?

24:09.582 --> 24:11.715
A friend.

24:11.717 --> 24:15.519
Maybe if you think of her
like that...

24:15.521 --> 24:16.854
Just a thought.

24:20.760 --> 24:21.926
Ow!

24:21.928 --> 24:23.093
Oh! Ohh!

24:23.095 --> 24:24.562
What the hell's going on?

24:24.564 --> 24:25.763
She crashed outside the scanner.

24:25.765 --> 24:27.631
W-what does that mean,
she crashed?

24:27.633 --> 24:29.550
What does that mean?! [ Groans ]

24:29.551 --> 24:31.468
Hey, listen, somebody
get harbert or Rorish here

24:31.471 --> 24:32.470
right now!

24:32.472 --> 24:33.671
I'll page them again. [ Groans ]

24:33.673 --> 24:35.506
Get me the ultrasound
and an I-stat.

24:35.508 --> 24:36.807
Risa: I think
she's bleeding internally.

24:36.809 --> 24:38.709
Oh, God!
It's like a knife in my belly!

24:38.711 --> 24:40.211
Oh, please, help me! Please!

24:40.213 --> 24:42.880
I need 2 liters n.S.
Wide-open through two 18s.

24:42.882 --> 24:44.682
Confirm
type and screen was sent.

24:44.684 --> 24:47.335
Thanks.
What's the story, Malaya?

24:47.336 --> 24:49.987
Mrs. Stein, 43. Came in
with increasing abdominal pain.

24:49.989 --> 24:51.989
Crumped in the C.T.
past medical problems?

24:51.991 --> 24:53.057
None. This is crazy.
She's healthy.

24:53.059 --> 24:54.058
What the hell is happening?

24:54.060 --> 24:55.159
Excuse me, excuse me.

24:55.161 --> 24:56.660
Oh, ed. Please, come on.

24:56.662 --> 24:57.828
Do something, please.

24:57.830 --> 24:59.797
Leanne, labs, imaging?
Crashed before C.T.

24:59.799 --> 25:00.698
U-preg?

25:00.700 --> 25:01.766
Test didn't come back yet.

25:01.767 --> 25:02.833
Uh, ultrasound now, please.

25:02.835 --> 25:04.201
[ Gasping ]

25:04.203 --> 25:07.137
Okay. Her uterus is empty,
but...

25:07.139 --> 25:08.522
What's wrong?!

25:08.523 --> 25:09.906
You<i> are</i> pregnant, Susan.

25:09.909 --> 25:11.709
It's ectopic. Ohhh!

25:11.711 --> 25:13.010
W-w-what is that? What is that?

25:13.012 --> 25:15.579
The embryo has planted itself
on the ovary.

25:15.581 --> 25:17.214
No, no, no.
It's worse, I'm afraid.

25:17.216 --> 25:18.682
It's ruptured,
and it's bleeding.

25:18.684 --> 25:19.517
Susan: Ohh!

25:19.519 --> 25:20.784
Susan...

25:20.786 --> 25:22.219
Get out!

25:22.221 --> 25:23.621
Leanne: Shh. What?

25:23.623 --> 25:24.989
I don't want you here!

25:24.990 --> 25:26.356
I'm not the one who did this,
okay? You decided...

25:26.357 --> 25:27.723
Son of a bitch!
Get out, get out!

25:27.727 --> 25:30.094
Mrs. Stein, lay down, please.
Mr. Stein, you need to...

25:30.096 --> 25:31.979
I'm not going anywhere.
That is my wife, okay?

25:31.980 --> 25:33.863
And it's<i> my</i> patient right now,
and I'm asking you to leave.

25:33.866 --> 25:35.900
Ed, I paid for this wing, okay?!

25:35.902 --> 25:37.701
Got it? Let's go.
Let's get her up to the O.R.

25:37.703 --> 25:38.903
Woman: Yes, doctor.
It's okay. Just breathe.

25:38.905 --> 25:40.704
Let's get her up to O.R.,
please.

25:40.706 --> 25:42.773
Watch her back. Okay, calm down.
Just breathe.

25:47.747 --> 25:51.148
¶¶

25:54.186 --> 25:55.252
[ door opens ]

25:57.323 --> 25:58.322
Is she okay?

25:58.324 --> 25:59.890
She's out of surgery.

25:59.892 --> 26:01.559
Is she okay?

26:01.561 --> 26:02.927
She's still asleep.

26:02.929 --> 26:04.695
The next few hours are critical.

26:04.697 --> 26:05.763
Well, I want to see her.

26:05.765 --> 26:07.487
I'm sorry, but...

26:07.488 --> 26:09.210
Where is she?
Take me to her right now.

26:09.211 --> 26:10.933
The last thing she said
before she lost consciousness

26:10.937 --> 26:12.297
was that she didn't
want you there.

26:12.939 --> 26:15.473
Leanne, she was angry.

26:15.474 --> 26:18.008
The law says he can't see her
until she says otherwise.

26:19.712 --> 26:20.978
I'm sorry.

26:22.815 --> 26:24.248
[ Door opens ]

26:24.250 --> 26:26.116
[ Door closes ]

26:26.118 --> 26:27.134
[ Monitor beeping ]

26:27.135 --> 26:28.151
Sandy: Thank you for doing this.

26:28.154 --> 26:30.287
Sure. It's still really hurting.

26:30.289 --> 26:33.023
Strange. Lidocaine
usually knocks out the pain.

26:33.025 --> 26:34.358
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ] I
don't know why it's not...

26:34.360 --> 26:35.793
[ flatline ]

26:35.795 --> 26:36.961
No pulse.

26:37.797 --> 26:39.964
No pulse.
Hannah, the crash cart!

26:39.966 --> 26:41.832
1 of epi. Slam it now.

26:41.834 --> 26:42.967
She's in arrest?
What the hell happened?

26:42.969 --> 26:44.469
What did you do?
Hannah, give me the bag.

26:44.470 --> 26:45.970
It's got to be an allergy.
I was giving her Lidocaine.

26:45.972 --> 26:47.671
She went into anaphylaxis.

26:47.673 --> 26:49.974
2%... that's too much.
Excuse me.

26:49.976 --> 26:52.009
It's not an allergy.
It's toxicity.

26:52.011 --> 26:54.011
What? No. It's an allergic
reaction. I gave her epi.

26:54.013 --> 26:55.379
Epi's not gonna work.
Hannah, I need intralipid.

26:55.381 --> 26:56.947
Intralipid? That's
what I said... now.

26:56.949 --> 26:58.716
It'll bind
to the excess Lidocaine.

26:58.718 --> 27:00.117
Hannah, bolus, then drip.

27:00.119 --> 27:03.020
Mario, start compressions.
I'll secure the airway.

27:04.090 --> 27:05.090
Come on.

27:06.659 --> 27:07.858
Hannah, you in?

27:07.860 --> 27:08.860
Press it.

27:10.730 --> 27:12.196
Mario, stop compressions.
Pulse check.

27:12.198 --> 27:14.098
[ Beeping slows ]

27:16.335 --> 27:17.768
Strong pulse.

27:17.770 --> 27:19.036
Yep.

27:19.038 --> 27:20.070
Welcome back, Sandy.

27:23.009 --> 27:25.643
Hey. Angus, wait up.

27:25.645 --> 27:27.111
Hey. You want to get a slice
after work?

27:27.113 --> 27:28.779
I'm, uh, just too amped
to go home.

27:28.781 --> 27:29.847
What's up with you?

27:29.849 --> 27:31.215
[ Water running ]
Uh, I'm crushing it.

27:31.217 --> 27:32.316
That's what's up with me.

27:32.318 --> 27:33.984
Did you see the save I just had?

27:33.986 --> 27:36.020
[ Water stops ] I'm sorry.
Let me be more specific.

27:36.022 --> 27:37.321
The most<i> recent</i> save I had?

27:37.323 --> 27:39.023
I'm sorry... didn't have
such a great view

27:39.025 --> 27:40.191
after you shoved me
out of the way.

27:40.192 --> 27:41.358
Oh, sorry. I didn't even notice.
I was just so amped.

27:41.360 --> 27:43.244
Amped?

27:43.245 --> 27:45.129
Look, we all make mistakes,
okay? Don't be embarrassed.

27:45.131 --> 27:46.430
Still a good team, though,
right?

27:47.933 --> 27:49.199
Right?

27:50.002 --> 27:51.168
Right.

27:56.709 --> 27:58.342
Craig. Come on in.

27:59.378 --> 28:00.711
Who are you?

28:00.713 --> 28:03.113
Officer combs.
I need to talk to you.

28:03.115 --> 28:04.815
Why? What else did he tell you?

28:04.817 --> 28:06.867
A lot.

28:06.868 --> 28:08.918
I'm warning you...
Don't trust this kid.

28:08.921 --> 28:10.954
We just need to understand
what happened.

28:10.956 --> 28:12.923
He's messing with them.
That's what's happening.

28:12.925 --> 28:14.091
What about
the burns on his arms?

28:14.093 --> 28:15.743
How do you think he got those?

28:15.744 --> 28:17.394
We had an issue
with him smoking cigarettes.

28:17.396 --> 28:19.129
He's been smuggling them in.

28:19.131 --> 28:21.331
Maybe he's burning himself.
They do all sorts of things.

28:23.135 --> 28:23.934
I got cutters... You name it.

28:23.935 --> 28:24.734
He came in badly dehydrated.

28:24.737 --> 28:26.403
He's been vomiting,
having seizures.

28:26.405 --> 28:28.355
That's often connected.

28:28.356 --> 28:30.306
Well, if he's dehydrated,
maybe he's not drinking water.

28:30.309 --> 28:31.408
He said that you were

28:31.410 --> 28:33.711
withholding water and food
from him.

28:33.713 --> 28:35.145
He says a lot of things.

28:35.147 --> 28:36.747
Why do you think
he's at this camp?

28:36.749 --> 28:38.148
He's lied his whole life.

28:38.150 --> 28:39.983
Call his parents. Ask them.

28:39.985 --> 28:42.086
They're in Europe.
We haven't heard back yet.

28:44.957 --> 28:46.423
Okay. You're free to go for now.

28:49.228 --> 28:50.394
[ Door opens ]

28:50.396 --> 28:52.362
That's it? [ Door closes ]

28:52.364 --> 28:53.997
So this guy just gets to walk?

29:09.381 --> 29:11.348
I talked to harbert
about the nurses.

29:11.350 --> 29:12.350
And?

29:13.919 --> 29:15.352
This isn't the year for it,
Jesse.

29:16.455 --> 29:17.921
Yeah, they always say that.

29:17.923 --> 29:19.223
Well, I looked at the budget.

29:19.225 --> 29:21.225
It's just not doable right now.

29:23.095 --> 29:25.095
"Nurse" comes
from the word "nourish."

29:25.097 --> 29:26.964
Did you know that?

29:26.965 --> 29:28.832
You develop the plan,
write the orders.

29:28.834 --> 29:30.167
We have your back.

29:30.169 --> 29:33.303
We double-check your doses,
cover your mistakes.

29:33.305 --> 29:34.872
We don't work for you, leanne.

29:34.874 --> 29:36.073
We<i> are</i> you.

29:36.075 --> 29:38.909
Your care depends on us.

29:38.911 --> 29:41.779
You think I don't know that?

29:42.782 --> 29:44.047
Can I ask you one thing?

29:45.184 --> 29:46.184
You fight for us?

29:47.186 --> 29:48.786
Of course I did.

29:48.788 --> 29:51.355
'Cause the leanne that I know
doesn't lose a fight.

30:04.036 --> 30:05.536
What room is he in?

30:05.538 --> 30:07.171
He's right in there.

30:09.441 --> 30:11.975
Uh, you guys go in.
I already saw him.

30:11.977 --> 30:12.876
Dad!

30:12.878 --> 30:14.411
Luke.

30:16.081 --> 30:18.148
[ Voice breaking ]
You look really bad.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.884
Well, you don't look so good
yourself, kid.

30:22.221 --> 30:24.221
I love you.

30:36.168 --> 30:37.467
What are you doing out here?

30:37.469 --> 30:39.236
Uh, trying to get
the insurance company

30:39.238 --> 30:40.838
to pay for his extended stay.

30:40.840 --> 30:42.106
Mm.

30:42.107 --> 30:43.373
He's gonna be here
for like a month, right?

30:43.375 --> 30:44.908
Yeah.

30:44.910 --> 30:46.109
Anyway...

30:47.446 --> 30:49.179
they needed some time alone.

30:49.181 --> 30:50.480
I hear you're getting married
in a week.

30:50.482 --> 30:52.616
Oh. [ Laughs ]
Not next week anymore.

30:54.019 --> 30:55.385
Uh, it's no big deal.

30:55.387 --> 30:57.187
It was gonna be really small.

30:57.189 --> 30:59.089
You know...'Cause...

31:00.392 --> 31:02.159
Luke's not on... on board yet,

31:02.161 --> 31:06.063
so Ben didn't want to freak him
out with a big wedding, and...

31:06.065 --> 31:08.065
[ Breathes shakily ] I'm sorry.

31:08.067 --> 31:09.633
Oh, hey, come on.
It's okay. It's okay.

31:09.635 --> 31:12.169
You know, I get it.

31:12.171 --> 31:15.272
His mother died four years ago.

31:15.274 --> 31:18.475
I just can't find a way in.

31:18.477 --> 31:20.477
I don't know how we're ever
gonna become a family.

31:23.215 --> 31:26.049
[ Chuckles ] Maybe I should go
to a zombie convention.

31:26.051 --> 31:27.551
[ Laughs ] Maybe you should.

31:27.553 --> 31:30.254
Look, he's... he's just a kid.

31:30.256 --> 31:32.422
Words are not gonna help.

31:32.424 --> 31:34.925
It's not his<i> brain</i>
you have to convince.

31:34.927 --> 31:36.427
It's his<i> heart.</i>

31:36.428 --> 31:37.928
Play around with him
in the sandbox.

31:37.930 --> 31:40.097
It's okay if he ignores you.

31:40.099 --> 31:43.200
But whatever you do,
don't give up on him, okay?

31:43.202 --> 31:45.035
That's the only way
you're gonna fail him.

31:45.037 --> 31:46.236
[ Thud, rattle ]
Guthrie: I need a gurney!

31:46.238 --> 31:48.372
He suddenly collapsed.

31:48.374 --> 31:50.440
Ben: Luke! Luke, Luke.

31:53.045 --> 31:54.411
Uh, Jesse, page the O.R. again.

31:54.413 --> 31:56.113
We need surgery down here now.

31:56.115 --> 31:57.281
What's happening to him?

31:57.283 --> 31:58.515
He's in shock.
His spleen is bleeding.

31:58.517 --> 31:59.800
He needs surgery.

31:59.801 --> 32:01.084
Damn it, this kid has no access.

32:01.086 --> 32:02.085
Here's your I.O. Drill.

32:02.087 --> 32:03.253
Thank you.

32:04.690 --> 32:05.923
Ready?

32:05.925 --> 32:08.058
[ Drill whirs ]

32:08.060 --> 32:09.993
Is that Mr. barton's son?

32:09.995 --> 32:11.028
What happened?

32:11.030 --> 32:13.697
Splenic laceration,
decompensated.

32:13.699 --> 32:16.199
Pressure's in the 70s. We've got
blood and fluids running.

32:16.201 --> 32:17.601
He needs to go up.

32:17.603 --> 32:18.969
I can clear O.R. 3.

32:18.971 --> 32:21.538
Notify the charge nurse,
Dr. pinkney.

32:21.540 --> 32:23.407
But what about Campbell?
He needs to sign off.

32:23.409 --> 32:25.042
He hasn't been returning
my pages.

32:25.044 --> 32:26.410
I don't care.

32:26.412 --> 32:27.411
Okay, let's go.

32:27.413 --> 32:30.447
Pack him up.
He's going to the O.R. now.

32:40.960 --> 32:43.327
[ Air hissing ]

32:44.330 --> 32:45.329
[ Monitors beeping ]

32:45.331 --> 32:46.363
Neal: Faster, please.

32:46.365 --> 32:48.398
Bougie, please.

32:48.400 --> 32:50.200
Suction, please. Dr. Hudson...

32:50.202 --> 32:51.335
What's going on in there?

32:51.337 --> 32:53.303
This is a child.

32:53.305 --> 32:54.671
He's lost a liter of blood...

32:54.673 --> 32:57.507
A child who couldn't wait
another second for a surgeon.

32:57.509 --> 32:59.643
[ Door opens ]

32:59.645 --> 33:01.244
What's your plan?

33:01.246 --> 33:05.382
My plan is to provide
what he needs... a splenectomy.

33:05.384 --> 33:06.616
Fire me if you want,

33:06.618 --> 33:08.752
but the boy needed a surgeon,
and he got one.

33:08.754 --> 33:10.320
Well, he's got one<i> now.</i>

33:10.322 --> 33:12.422
Dr. pinkney, please move over.

33:15.160 --> 33:16.493
Suture.

33:17.763 --> 33:19.363
I'm not going to fire you.

33:19.365 --> 33:21.164
You had to start without me.
I get it.

33:23.002 --> 33:24.167
Tie here and cut.

33:25.671 --> 33:28.171
Yes, you. Tie it.

33:35.314 --> 33:38.015
I've endured
your patronizing tone,

33:38.017 --> 33:39.316
your pointless tests,

33:39.318 --> 33:41.618
and your continued attempts
to humiliate me.

33:41.620 --> 33:43.053
Oh, so you think
you've been tested?

33:43.055 --> 33:44.021
I've been tested
by leanne Rorish.

33:44.023 --> 33:45.188
You'll never come close.

33:45.190 --> 33:47.157
She's a great doctor.

33:47.159 --> 33:48.408
But she's not a surgeon.

33:48.409 --> 33:49.658
I see. No, you<i> don't</i> see.

33:49.661 --> 33:52.696
Emergency medicine
is blue-collar work.

33:52.698 --> 33:54.364
So I've been told.

33:54.366 --> 33:56.299
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

33:56.301 --> 33:59.069
Down there, it's all about
the first 10 minutes.

33:59.071 --> 34:01.371
Stop the bleeding,
plug the holes,

34:01.373 --> 34:04.074
and do it all fast enough
to keep them alive.

34:04.076 --> 34:07.144
See, but up here,
precision is what matters.

34:07.146 --> 34:09.246
Down there, it's all about
bougies and sutures

34:09.248 --> 34:11.181
and duct tape.

34:11.183 --> 34:14.751
In here, it's about hands.

34:14.753 --> 34:17.254
Hands? Yeah.

34:17.255 --> 34:19.756
So far, all you've shown me
are the hands of a carpenter.

34:19.758 --> 34:21.625
What I'm waiting to see is

34:21.627 --> 34:24.494
if you have
the hands of an artist.

34:26.131 --> 34:27.297
Suture.

34:28.400 --> 34:30.333
[ Grunting ]

34:31.570 --> 34:33.737
He won't stop seizing.
Did he get the ativan?

34:33.739 --> 34:35.105
Yes. Just pushed it.

34:35.107 --> 34:36.206
He's been seizing?

34:36.208 --> 34:37.274
Multiple times.

34:37.275 --> 34:38.341
His workup's been normal,
though, right?

34:38.343 --> 34:40.243
Electrolytes, tox?

34:40.245 --> 34:41.695
Yeah. All normal.

34:41.696 --> 34:43.146
I've been giving him ativan
for the seizures.

34:43.148 --> 34:44.731
[ Muffled grunting ]
Hannah, get the Keppra.

34:44.732 --> 34:46.315
I got an airway kit ready.
I think we need to intubate.

34:46.318 --> 34:47.250
Hold on.

34:47.252 --> 34:49.152
[ Grunting ]

34:53.158 --> 34:54.691
Brody, you can stop seizing now.

34:54.693 --> 34:56.977
What are you doing?

34:56.978 --> 34:59.262
Brody, stop seizing now.
You're not fooling anyone.

34:59.264 --> 35:00.530
If your seizures were real,

35:00.531 --> 35:01.797
then your hand
would have hit your face.

35:01.800 --> 35:02.632
Google it.

35:02.634 --> 35:03.767
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:03.769 --> 35:05.268
I can't believe
you're saying this.

35:05.270 --> 35:07.270
What are you accusing me of?

35:07.272 --> 35:09.739
So, what'd you take
to make yourself vomit?

35:09.741 --> 35:11.374
Ipecac? Saltwater?

35:11.376 --> 35:13.543
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:15.347 --> 35:16.413
Eye drops.

35:18.250 --> 35:19.883
Makes your heart rate
go up, too.

35:19.885 --> 35:21.151
Google it.

35:21.153 --> 35:23.720
I love the ativan, by the way.
Hell of a high.

35:23.722 --> 35:25.155
Why would you do this?

35:25.157 --> 35:26.640
Why not?

35:26.641 --> 35:28.124
You accused an innocent man
of abusing you.

35:28.127 --> 35:30.527
Yeah, nobody's innocent, doc.

35:33.232 --> 35:34.181
Yeah, nice try.

35:34.182 --> 35:35.131
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
Brody?

35:35.467 --> 35:36.800
Sat is 80%.

35:38.403 --> 35:39.820
Come on.

35:39.821 --> 35:41.238
He has no gag. Get the airway.

35:41.240 --> 35:42.906
How much ativan
did you give him?

35:42.908 --> 35:44.174
10 milligrams.

35:44.176 --> 35:45.308
10? That's a horse's dosage.

35:45.310 --> 35:46.910
I thought
he was in refractory seizures.

35:46.912 --> 35:48.578
Grab the flumazenil.

35:50.315 --> 35:51.882
Wait.

35:55.521 --> 35:57.587
Just wait. Wait.

35:57.589 --> 35:59.189
[ Beeping slows ] Sats rising.

35:59.191 --> 36:00.790
[ Sighs ]

36:00.792 --> 36:03.293
How did you know he was faking?

36:03.295 --> 36:05.395
I spent a year in Haiti.

36:05.397 --> 36:08.165
I know what a kid living
on rice and water looks like.

36:08.167 --> 36:09.666
It's not him.

36:13.305 --> 36:15.839
I remember what it was like
to be a resident.

36:15.841 --> 36:17.407
I would have treated him
for seizures, too.

36:17.409 --> 36:18.475
[ Scoffs ]

36:29.188 --> 36:32.355
All right. Looks good.

36:32.357 --> 36:33.657
[ Sighs ]

36:33.659 --> 36:35.258
You okay?

36:35.260 --> 36:38.428
I can't believe
I almost got a kid killed today.

36:40.232 --> 36:42.666
I think I let her
get under my skin.

36:43.635 --> 36:45.368
You know, she's not
your enemy, Christa.

37:05.290 --> 37:06.957
Go ahead. It's okay.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.233
When is she gonna wake up?

37:16.235 --> 37:18.235
The anesthesia
should wear off soon.

37:18.237 --> 37:19.469
She's cold.

37:19.471 --> 37:20.604
She's comfortable.

37:24.243 --> 37:25.308
[ Sighs ]

37:28.413 --> 37:30.513
We bought furniture
three different times...

37:30.515 --> 37:33.750
Three different cribs...

37:33.752 --> 37:36.820
Three changing tables.

37:36.822 --> 37:39.022
Each time, we were so excited.

37:40.692 --> 37:42.609
And each time,

37:42.610 --> 37:44.810
I had to have somebody come
and take the furniture away.

37:47.799 --> 37:52.335
The more we tried and failed,
the more irritated I got.

37:52.337 --> 37:53.570
I just wanted it
to stop already,

37:53.572 --> 37:54.638
but she...

37:54.640 --> 37:56.640
[ Smooches ]

37:56.642 --> 37:58.041
Just refused to.

38:00.379 --> 38:02.612
Instead of making me proud,

38:02.614 --> 38:08.485
proud of
how damn determined she was...

38:08.487 --> 38:10.487
I hated her for it.

38:13.525 --> 38:15.625
Listen, Robert,
you can't do this to yourself.

38:16.595 --> 38:18.962
When she wakes up,

38:18.963 --> 38:21.330
she's gonna be devastated
that she lost another one.

38:21.333 --> 38:22.532
[ Sniffles ]

38:26.405 --> 38:27.771
The last one.

38:27.773 --> 38:30.607
Or...

38:30.609 --> 38:32.542
Maybe losing the last one
is the best thing

38:32.544 --> 38:34.544
that could have happened
to you both.

38:38.483 --> 38:40.417
Look at you.

38:40.419 --> 38:41.785
[ Chuckles ]

38:41.787 --> 38:43.853
When is the last time
you held her hand like that?

38:45.324 --> 38:46.623
You love her.

38:47.759 --> 38:50.493
Maybe you forgot that.

38:52.497 --> 38:54.497
I do. I really do.

38:58.370 --> 38:59.769
[ Sighs, smooches ]

38:59.771 --> 39:02.005
But it's too late. I lost her.

39:02.007 --> 39:02.806
Robert.

39:02.808 --> 39:04.574
[ Sniffles ]

39:06.845 --> 39:09.646
[ Drowsily ] Robbie?

39:09.648 --> 39:11.581
Hey.

39:11.583 --> 39:13.750
I love you, too.

39:13.752 --> 39:15.485
Ohh!

39:17.522 --> 39:19.122
Mm.

39:19.124 --> 39:20.957
I love you, honey.

39:20.959 --> 39:22.359
Mm. I'm here.

39:22.361 --> 39:24.394
Mm.

39:24.396 --> 39:25.462
[ Sniffles ]

39:25.464 --> 39:27.797
I'm not going anywhere.

39:35.374 --> 39:37.907
So... <i>That's</i> how it works.

39:39.378 --> 39:41.478
The laws don't apply
to the V.I.P.S?

39:42.848 --> 39:44.481
He's not a V.I.P. Right now.

39:46.952 --> 39:48.585
No.

39:48.587 --> 39:50.453
You're right. He's not.

39:50.455 --> 39:53.656
You should come down here
more often.

39:53.658 --> 39:55.658
It's not the same, is it?

39:55.660 --> 39:58.428
Up there, it's all...

39:58.430 --> 40:02.499
Budgets and numbers and charts.

40:02.501 --> 40:04.501
Down here, it's people.

40:06.671 --> 40:09.906
¶¶

40:11.676 --> 40:13.676
[ siren wailing ]

40:13.678 --> 40:15.745
[ Radio chatter ]

40:24.089 --> 40:26.790
That's the bite that turned you.

40:26.792 --> 40:27.791
Turned me where?

40:27.793 --> 40:29.426
You can't become a zombie

40:29.428 --> 40:31.094
unless you get bitten by one
first.

40:31.096 --> 40:32.862
Everybody knows that.

40:32.864 --> 40:33.663
Sorry.

40:33.665 --> 40:35.198
So, what's next?

40:35.200 --> 40:36.766
Bullet wound to the brain?

40:36.768 --> 40:38.601
No. Then you'd be dead.

40:38.603 --> 40:39.869
But I<i> am</i> dead.

40:39.871 --> 40:42.205
No, you're<i> undead.</i>

40:42.206 --> 40:44.540
If you destroy the brain,
then the zombie's<i> dead</i> dead.

40:44.543 --> 40:45.942
You can't be<i> dead</i> dead.

40:45.944 --> 40:47.877
Zombie 101.

40:47.879 --> 40:49.979
[ Chuckles ]

40:49.980 --> 40:52.080
You know, I got to admit,
this was a first for me.

40:52.083 --> 40:54.451
Well, at least we didn't
make you dress up, right?

40:54.453 --> 40:55.552
[ Laughs ]

40:55.554 --> 40:57.720
Wow! You look great.

40:57.722 --> 40:58.688
Thanks.

40:58.690 --> 41:00.557
So does your mother.

41:00.559 --> 41:02.826
She's not my mother.

41:05.897 --> 41:08.698
She's my friend.

41:19.044 --> 41:20.610
You guys ready? Ben: Yep.

41:20.612 --> 41:22.912
Whoa.
You went total brain-eater.

41:22.914 --> 41:23.847
Yeah.

41:23.849 --> 41:25.482
This is gonna be so cool.

41:25.484 --> 41:27.250
You got the ring?

41:28.487 --> 41:29.619
Yep.

41:29.621 --> 41:32.222
Okay. Showtime.

41:32.224 --> 41:33.590
You nervous?

41:33.592 --> 41:35.625
A little. [ Chuckles ]

41:35.627 --> 41:37.677
Thanks for everything.

41:37.678 --> 41:39.728
You got it, living-dead person.

41:39.731 --> 41:41.764
Let's go. Come on.

41:48.640 --> 41:50.106
You look beautiful.

41:51.176 --> 41:52.842
Jesse and I did that.

41:54.579 --> 41:56.746
Well, shall we begin?

41:56.748 --> 41:58.081
We shall.

42:00.652 --> 42:01.684
You ready?

42:01.686 --> 42:03.553
Jesse: Ready, ready.

42:05.690 --> 42:07.857
Guthrie: We are gathered here

42:07.859 --> 42:12.562
to join Ben barton
and Leslie Garcia together

42:12.564 --> 42:14.898
as husband and wife.

42:14.900 --> 42:19.702
The family of Ben and Luke
will not change.

42:19.704 --> 42:21.237
It'll just get bigger.
